com.google.api.ads.dfp.v201311

Class ExchangeRate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.api.ads.dfp.v201311.ExchangeRate
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ExchangeRate
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    An ExchangeRate represents a currency which is one of the Network.secondaryCurrencyCodes, and the latest exchange rate between this currency and Network.currencyCode.

      • getExchangeRate

        public java.lang.Long getExchangeRate()
        Gets the exchangeRate value for this ExchangeRate.
        Returns:
        exchangeRate * The latest exchange rate at the refreshRate and in the direction. The value is stored as the exchange rate times 10,000,000,000 truncated to a long. When the refreshRate is ExchangeRateRefreshRate.FIXED, this attribute is required. When it is not, this attribute is readonly and is assigned by Google with the exchange rate for the latest time period.
